You can change MedusWiki page layout in two ways. First is to modify CSS file and second is to modify or create new templates.
----
!! Changing CSS file 
* open ''index.py'' file in text editor.
* find string:
 cfg['css'] = "http://meduswiki.berlios.de/meduswiki.css"
* enter new link.
Copy of meduswiki css file is placed at:
 templates/meduswiki.css
----
!! Modifying TAL templates
MedusWiki uses TAL template language, witch originated from [http://www.zope.org|Zope] (ZPT). If you want to learn more about TAL, read [http://dev.zope.org/Wikis/DevSite/Projects/ZPT/SimpleTutorial|introductory guide to Zope Page Templates]

By default MedusWiki is in ''xtm'' mode (uses ''topic maps''). In this case, these templates are used:
 templates/xtm/
             changes.zpt (RecentChanges page)
             edit.zpt (Edit page)
             print.zpt (Print page)
             search.zpt (Search page)
             toc.zpt (TitleIndex page)
             view.zpt (Wiki page)
In case then MedusWiki is in ''zpt'' mode, templates located in this directory are used:
 templates/zpt/
(Read [?CoderGuide|Coder Guide]) to get more information about modes.